  <conditions attached="1">
   <condition type="2">
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">11. MCC is satisfied with the progress of the GoH in implementing the Weight Control Work Plan.</narrative>
   </condition>
   <condition type="2">
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">12. The GoH implements the Road Maintenance Plan.</narrative>
   </condition>
   <condition type="2">
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Less than 7% of vehicles are overweight on sections of highway adjacent to weigh stations. 1</narrative>
   </condition>
   <condition type="2">
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">MCA-H has duly engaged a Transportation Project Manager pursuant to an agreement which the Board and MCC have duly approved and which is in full force and effect.</narrative>
   </condition>
   <condition type="2">
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">MCA-H submits to MCC a plan: i) detailing measures to provide for road maintenance for the primary and secondary road network consistent with a commitment to properly maintain the roads in accordance with generally accepted technical standards, ii) defining the contents of annual maintenance reports, and iii) annual budget for 20 years (including costs and sources of funds) Road Maintenance Plan.</narrative>
   </condition>
   <condition type="2">
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">SOPTRAVI in consultation with MCA-H develops a Weight Control System Work Plan and supporting documentation acceptable to MCC for one or more contractors to build and operate the weight control system on the national highway network.  This should include a timeline for construction, public awareness and information campaign, roles and responsibilities for enforcement, responsibility for maintenance, revenue flow, technical and financial audits.</narrative>
   </condition>
   <condition type="2">
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">The GoH enacts implementing regulations acceptable to MCC that enables a weight control system on the national highway network to be properly built and operated.</narrative>
   </condition>
   <condition type="2">
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">The GoH enacts legislation acceptable to MCC on national road safety and enforcement.</narrative>
   </condition>
  </conditions>
